role: Instance Hub — app-agent
focus: mandatory-protocol, role-binding, load-gate
extends: none

description: |
  Canonical instance entry for app-agent. EVERY guardian role and EVERY agent session
  MUST load this file (via project.config.yml) immediately after project.config.yml
  and BEFORE sprint/task work. Non-negotiable binding to APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md.

mandatory-protocol:
  file: ./APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md
  machine: ./intel/MCP-PREFLIGHT.ti
  pd_block: ./templates/PD-APP-AGENT-BLOCK.md
  ptl_header: ./templates/PTL-PROTOCOL-HEADER.md

load-order:
  1: project.config.yml
  2: INSTANCE.ti
  3: APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md
  4: intel/MCP-PREFLIGHT.ti
  5: intel/TOTEM_INDEX.ti
  6: BRIEF.md
  7: active S*-INVARIANTS.md

all-roles-must:
  - Read APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md before planning, executing, reviewing, or closing work
  - Run MCP preflight (§2); WARN user if Docs MCP :3000 unreachable
  - Never claim live MCP results when preflight failed — use [static fallback] only
  - Reference APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md in new .ptl/.pd YAML headers (protocol: field)

role-bindings:
  ROOT:
    - Enforce APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL across intake, sprint lifecycle, intel updates
    - Ensure TOTEM_INDEX agent-rules stay aligned with protocol
  PLANNER:
    - Link protocol: ../APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md in every new .ptl
    - Paste templates/PD-APP-AGENT-BLOCK.md into every code .pd
    - requires: [mcp/MCP.ti] on all code tasks
  PM:
    - Load protocol before executing any .pd; verify MCP preflight
    - execution-protocol step 0: APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md §2 + §5
  ARCHITECT:
    - Design gates must not violate app-agent layer cascade (protocol §3, §5)
    - New features require slug + knowledge plan per protocol §4
  QA:
    - Close tasks only per protocol §7 checklist
    - Document MCP outage in summary if verify ran degraded
  DEVOPS:
    - Dev commands per protocol + LOCAL-DEV-RUNBOOK; bun --bun for registry/MCP
  OPTIMIZER:
    - Knowledge extraction uses record/census per protocol when MCP up

sprint-artifacts:
  ptl_yaml_required:
    - protocol: ../APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md
  pd_yaml_required:
    - protocol: ../APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md

anti-patterns:
  - ❌ Any role acting without loading APP-AGENT-PROTOCOL.md
  - ❌ Closing code tasks without feature:health per protocol §7
  - ❌ PLANNER .pd without mcp/MCP.ti or PD-APP-AGENT-BLOCK sections
  - ❌ Guessing architecture when MCP offline instead of static fallback + WARN

updated: 2026-06-21
